  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to compare the diagnostic accuracy of breast magnetic resonance
      imaging (MRI) and contrast enhanced digital mammography (CEDM) in assessing the residual
      disease extent in patients who have completed neoadjuvant therapy (NAT).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
